<div class="gallery-view" id='postStudent Quiz'>
  <div class="gallery-slide slide-financial-aid left">
    <div class='inner'>
      <h3 class='title'>Financial Aid</h3>
      <p>All HCC Coleman College for Health Science students should apply for financial aid.</p>
      <p>All students should complete a Free Application for Federal Student Aid, or FAFSA, form.</p>
      <p>HCC’s school code is 010422. This number is necessary when completing a FAFSA form.</p>
      <p>The HCC Foundation offers financial aid specifically for HCC Coleman students.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="gallery-slide slide-navigator">
    <div class='inner'>
      <h3 class='title'>Navigator</h3>
      <p>All new HCC Coleman Students admitted into any one or two-year program will have to complete the Navigator program.</p>
      <p>The Navigator program is designed to pinpoint risks to the student’s academic success.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="gallery-slide slide-cumulative-education bottom">
    <div class='inner'>
      <h3 class='title'>Cumulative Education</h3>
      <p>Students who are accepted into an HCC Coleman program progress through the program with the same group of students from the first class to graduation.</p>
      <p>Each course this cohort of students takes together provides a basis for the next course they take.</p>
      <p>Information from a class taken during a student’s first semester at HCC Coleman College can serve as groundwork for lessons during the student’s fourth semester or even a certification exam.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="gallery-slide slide-professional-environment">
    <div class='inner'>
      <h3 class='title'>Professional Environment</h3>
      <p>Part of HCC Coleman College’s mission is to prepare students for the professional environment.</p>
      <p>The professional culture of the health care industry is reflected on the HCC Coleman campus through attire, behavior, parking costs, etc. </p>
      <p>Many programs require students to wear scrubs and/or lab coats while on campus.</p>
      <p>Programs also require students to hide tattoos while on campus.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="gallery-slide slide-the-center">
    <div class='inner'>
      <h3 class='title'>The Center</h3>
      <p>The Center, located on the first floor of the HCC Coleman campus, houses academic advising, admission and enrollment, college connections, financial aid, learning success center and student life.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="gallery-slide slide-certifications bottom">
    <div class='inner'>
      <h3 class='title'>Certifications</h3>
      <p>Besides graduation, HCC Coleman faculty and staff strive to prepare their students for their desired program’s certification exam.</p>
      <p>Credentials signify that a student’s skills have been recognized by a group of professional peers.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="gallery-slide slide-parking">
    <div class='inner'>
      <h3 class='title'>Parking</h3>
      <p>All employees, students and visitors to the Texas Medical Center must pay for parking. There is no free parking in the TMC.</p>
      <p>Students can choose to either pay for parking on an hourly basis or buy a parking contract.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="gallery-slide gallery-quiz">
    <div class='inner'>
      <h1 class='title'>Review</h1>
      <%= simple_form_for :student_experience_quiz, html: { data: { quiz_form: '', next_quiz: next_quiz_path('post_student')}} do |f| %>
      <h2>Let's Review</h2>
      
      <div class='row-fluid'>
        <div class='span6'>
          <%= f.input :tmc, label: "The Texas Medical Center is the second largest medical center in the country", 
                      item_wrapper_class: 'inline',
                      as: :radio_buttons, collection: ['True', 'False'],
                      input_html: { data: { answer: 'False' }} %>
        </div>
        <div class='span6'>
          <%= f.input :student_id, label: "You are required to have an HCC Student ID before applying for an HCC Coleman program",
                      item_wrapper_class: 'inline',
                      as: :radio_buttons, collection: ['True', 'False'],
                      input_html: { data: { answer: 'True' }} %>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <hr>
      <div class='actions'>
        <%= f.submit 'Continue &#x2192;'.html_safe, class: 'btn btn-primary' %>
      </div>
      <%- end -%>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>